Preserve ``URI`` value parameters on a jCal round-trip. :meth:`vUri.from_jcal <icalendar.prop.uri.vUri.from_jcal>` previously passed the parameters positionally, but ``vUri.__new__`` takes ``encoding`` as its second positional parameter. As a result, the ``URI`` value parameters were consumed as ``encoding`` and dropped. For example, ``ATTACH;FMTTYPE=...`` or ``CONFERENCE;FEATURE=...`` lost their parameters. They are now passed as the ``params`` keyword. Prepared with the assistance of an AI coding agent (Anthropic's Claude Opus 4.8). @gaoflow
